	abstract = {In this paper we propose the use of commercial websites and a contextualized weak supervision framework as an alternative to industrial taxonomies to identify and classify digital industrial activity. Despite the crucial importance of industrial taxonomies for government and research, their static nature leaves taxonomies 
unable to accurately capture a country’s industrial structure. This is particularly problematic in the context for firms producing novel, digital outputs, which are nowadays classified into the wrong industrial sectors and thus rendered almost invisible to official statistics. To address this issue we show how commercial  websites can complement, or even substitute industrial classification surveys and
